{"parse":{"title":"Scholarship Examination","pageid":19509669,"revid":830755561,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Scholarship Examination</b> (also known as the <b>Grade 5 exam</b>) is a highly competitive <a href=\"/wiki/Sri_Lanka\" title=\"Sri Lanka\">Sri Lankan</a> examination conducted by the <a href=\"/wiki/Department_of_Examinations\" title=\"Department of Examinations\">Department of Examinations</a> of the <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Education_(Sri_Lanka)\" title=\"Ministry of Education (Sri Lanka)\">Ministry of Education</a>. It is optional for students to undertake it during the final year of <a href=\"/wiki/Education_in_Sri_Lanka#Primary\" title=\"Education in Sri Lanka\">primary school</a> (Grade 5 (usually ages 9\u201310)). Based on the results of the exam, students could transfer to prominent national schools. The exams are held in two mediums: <a href=\"/wiki/Sinhala_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sinhala language\">Sinhala</a>,  and tamil\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#School_rankings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">School rankings</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Controversies\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Controversies</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Scholarship_Examination&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The examinations were introduced by the late Hon. Dr. <a href=\"/wiki/C.W.W._Kannangara\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"C.W.W. Kannangara\">C.W.W. Kannangara</a>, who took the initiative in establishing <a href=\"/wiki/Free_education\" title=\"Free education\">free education</a> when he was the Minister of Education. Under this initiative the government established <a href=\"/wiki/Madhya_Maha_Vidyalayas\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Madhya Maha Vidyalayas\">Madhya Maha Vidyalayas</a> (MMV - Central Colleges) that were scattered around the island. The Scholarship Examination was a means for gifted students from villages to move to better schools with government scholarships.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"School_rankings\">School rankings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Scholarship_Examination&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: School rankings\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Update\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"Ambox current red.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Ambox_current_red.svg/42px-Ambox_current_red.svg.png\" width=\"42\" height=\"34\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Ambox_current_red.svg/63px-Ambox_current_red.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Ambox_current_red.svg/84px-Ambox_current_red.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"360\" data-file-height=\"290\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This section needs to be <b>updated</b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please update this article to reflect recent events or newly available information.</span>  <small><i>(November 2017)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div>\n<dl><dt>Boys Schools</dt></dl><ol><li><a href=\"/wiki/Royal_College_Colombo\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Royal College Colombo\">Royal College</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Colombo_07&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Colombo 07 (page does not exist)\">Colombo 07</a> (marks 187)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Dharmaraja_College\" title=\"Dharmaraja College\">Dharmaraja College</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Kandy\" title=\"Kandy\">Kandy</a> (marks 186)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Maliyadeva_College\" title=\"Maliyadeva College\">Maliyadeva Boy's College</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Kurunegala\" title=\"Kurunegala\">Kurunegala</a>(marks 186)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Ananda_College\" title=\"Ananda College\">Ananda College</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Colombo_10&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Colombo 10 (page does not exist)\">Colombo 10</a> (marks 184)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Nalanda_College,_Colombo\" title=\"Nalanda College, Colombo\">Nalanda College</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Colombo_10&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Colombo 10 (page does not exist)\">Colombo 10</a> (marks 182)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/D._S._Senanayake_College\" title=\"D. S. Senanayake College\">D. S. Senanayake College</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Colombo_07&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Colombo 07 (page does not exist)\">Colombo 07</a> (marks 180)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Mahinda_College\" title=\"Mahinda College\">Mahinda College</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Galle\" title=\"Galle\">Galle</a> (marks 180)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=St.Sylvester_College&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"St.Sylvester College (page does not exist)\">St.Sylvester College</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Kandy\" title=\"Kandy\">Kandy</a> (marks 180)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Isipathana_College\" title=\"Isipathana College\">Isipathana College</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Colombo_05&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Colombo 05 (page does not exist)\">Colombo 05</a> (marks 178)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Thurstan_College\" title=\"Thurstan College\">Thurstan College</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Colombo_03&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Colombo 03 (page does not exist)\">Colombo 03</a> (marks 176)</li></ol><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Controversies\">Controversies</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Scholarship_Examination&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Controversies\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2><p>In recent years the exam has become extremely competitive, therefore many claim that it puts unnecessary pressure on students at an early age. It has been considered as a \"parent's\" exam rather than student's. It is necessary to carry out a study on the long term success of the scholars.\n</p><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Scholarship_Examination&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2><div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.moe.gov.lk/english/images/grade_5/2017/sin_boy.pdf\">http://www.moe.gov.lk/english/images/grade_5/2017/sin_boy.pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div><table class=\"multicol\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; padding: 0; border: 0; background:transparent; width:100%;\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<tbody><tr><td></td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2232\nCached time: 20180913155709\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.076 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.104 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 228/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 4196/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 704/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 11/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 461/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.024/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 834 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   67.086      1 -total\n 86.03%   57.713      1 Template:Update\n 54.86%   36.806      2 Template:Main_other\n 51.37%   34.464      1 Template:Ambox\n  9.64%    6.470      1 Template:Reflist\n  2.75%    1.843      1 Template:SUBJECTSPACE_formatted\n  2.60%    1.744      1 Template:Col-begin\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:19509669-0!canonical and timestamp 20180913155709 and revision id 830755561\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[{"lang":"si","url":"https://si.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%80_%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B7%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%9C%E0%B6%BA","langname":"Sinhala","autonym":"\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0d82\u0dc4\u0dbd","*":"\u0dc1\u0dd2\u0dc2\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db7\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dba"}],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Wikipedia_articles_in_need_of_updating_from_November_2017"},{"sortkey":"","hidden":""